cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MA, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

The paper discusses viral campaigns in social networks, which falls under the category of social media and online communities. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the behaviour of individual community members, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Sociological Aspects of Computing). The use of data and experimental results could also suggest cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential negative effects of incentivised campaigns, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
